en_132217_0	Minister of Provincial Councils and Local Government Faizer Mustapha stated that the government will hold Local Government (LG) Elections in the first quarter of 2017.
en_132217_1	Speaking to the media today he said that the questions regarding delimitation will be resorted by next month.
en_132217_2	The government had insisted that it will not hold the election under the present electoral system.
en_132217_3	The delimitation has been done to introduce the new electoral system, but there were many complaints regarding the delimitation, the government also says.
en_132217_4	President Maithripala Sirisena also gave an assurance recently that the LG polls will be held early next year.
